<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Japan-Capsize     11-19 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Capsize,0201</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Panamaniam Ship Sinks Near Taiwan, 17 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Panamanian cargo ship sank early Saturday during a
storm in the East China Sea near Taiwan, and 17 Filipino crew
members were missing and feared dead, coast guard officials said.
   A Japanese tanker rescued three of the 20 crew members from the
La Vie en Rose, a 4,415-ton vessel loaded with Malaysian timber,
said a coast guard official in Okinawa.
   The offical said a coast guard plane was dispatched to the scene
of the accident at dawn Saturday but found no traces of the missing
crew. A patrol boat also was due at the scene later Saturday.
   Authorities said they received a distress call from the Taiwanese
coast guard late Friday that the vessel was sinking 168 miles east
of Taiwan near the Okinawan island chain. The boat sank at 12:42
a.m. Saturday, officials said.
   The cargo vessel was bound for northern Japan when it began
taking on water, the coast guard said.
   According to the official, all 20 Filipino crew members escaped
the sinking ship in lifeboats but only three were found by a passing
tanker in waters described as rough.
</TEXT>
