<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Much as we have made in the way of progress against racial
discrimination, gender discrimination, enforcement of the Bill of
Rights _ great as that progress has been _ there's still so much
still to be done.'' _ Supreme Court Justice William J. Brennan Jr.,
addressing lawyers and judges at the beginning a yearlong
bicentennial celebration of the federal court system.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``A lame duck trying to rescue a dead duck.'' _ Canadian Liberal
Party leader John Turner, deriding President Reagan's defense of the
U.S.-Canada free trade agreement, which he is making an issue in his
election campaign against Prime Minister Brian Mulroney.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``Four years is a long time. Eight years is twice as long.'' _
National Democratic Party Chairman Paul Kirk, responding to party
officials' expressed desire to have him serve another term in the
top post.
