<HEAD>British Jet Gets Stuck After Landing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British jet with 320 people on board became
partly stuck in mud after landing at Gatwick airport early Saturday,
but there were no injuries, officials said.
   Another aircraft was diverted while the Dan-Air Airbus, which had
flown from Tenerife in the Canary Islands, was towed away, said
Gatwick spokeswoman Carol Hill.
   She said the jet turned off the main runway to taxi into the
airport when one of its wheel sections went off the pavement.
   Passengers were taken by bus into the terminal from the plane,
she said.
   Peter Clegg, a spokesman for Dan-Air, said it was not known why
the aircraft went off the taxiway, but said ``it was going slowly.
It didn't skid.''
